<table>
<tr>
<td>
  
**Shotgun is a CLI tool** that generates codebase-aware specs for AI coding agents like Cursor, Claude Code, and Lovable. **It reads your entire repository**, researches how new features should fit your architecture, and produces technical specifications that keep AI agents on trackâ€”so they build what you actually want instead of derailing halfway through. **Bring your own key (BYOK) or use a Shotgun subscription â€” $10 for $10 in usage.**

It includes research on existing patterns, implementation plans that respect your architecture, and task breakdowns ready to export as **AGENTS.md** files. Each spec is complete enough that your AI agent can work longer and further without losing context or creating conflicts.

<p align="center">
  <img src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9c7ca014-1ed3-4935-b310-9147b275fdc7" alt="Shotgun Demo" />
</p>

</td>
</tr>
</table>

